      "role": "user",
      "content": "psychosomatic? i don't know, man. it didn't feel like anxiety. it felt like a data stream. it was a precise, rhythmic pulse that matched the sell-off timing perfectly. like my nervous system was picking up the electromagnetic frequency of the trade executions. if it's just stress, why was it so specific to the exact millisecond the dip started? it's like i'm actually sensing the digital signal.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
